import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['open'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the trend of daily closing prices over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['volume'] = pd.to_numeric(data['volume'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.gca()
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.hist(data['volume'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
